{
  "texts": [
    "This process is iterated until the noise is completely removed, resulting in the generation of a new image which resembles the training data distribution.",
    "In general diffusion models are easier to train compared to GANs, due to more traditional loss functions, but are much slower at generating images.",
    "The openly available code of each generative model was modified to generate 5-channel images instead of 3 channels, no other modifications to the default architectures were done.",
    "Each generative model will thereby learn to jointly generate the four MR images (T1w, T1wGD, T2w, FLAIR) and the corresponding tumor annotation at the same time.",
    "There is no guarantee that the synthetic annotations will be restricted to the same values as the real annotations ([51,102,204])."
  ]
}